com.thomsonreuters.upa.codec

Class RefreshMsgFlags

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.thomsonreuters.upa.codec.RefreshMsgFlags

  • public class RefreshMsgFlags
extends java.lang.Object
    A combination of bit values that indicate special behaviors and the presence of optional RefreshMsg content.
    See Also:
    RefreshMsg

      • SOLICITED

        public static final int SOLICITED
        (0x0020) Indicates that the refresh is sent as a response to a request, referred to as a solicited refresh. A refresh sent to inform a consumer of an upstream change in information (i.e., an unsolicited refresh) must not include this flag.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • REFRESH_COMPLETE

        public static final int REFRESH_COMPLETE
        (0x0040) Indicates that the message is the final part of the RefreshMsg. This flag value should be set when:
        • The message is a single-part refresh (i.e., atomic refresh).
        • The message is the final part of a multi-part refresh.
        See Also:
